---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="Free BMI Calculator Online - Check BMI by Age, Weight, Men & Women | BMICalc"
  description="Calculate your Body Mass Index instantly with our free BMI calculator online. Get tailored weight results for men, women, and seniors using kg with age."
  keywords="bmi calculator, bmi calculator online, bmi calculator women, bmi calculator men, bmi calculator female, bmi calculator male, bmi calculator kg with age, bmi calculator by age"
  canonicalUrl="https://calbmi.com/"
>
  <Fragment slot="head">
    <!-- Structured Data (JSON-LD) -->
    <script type="application/ld+json" is:inline>
    {
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "WebApplication",
      "name": "BMICalc - Body Mass Index Calculator",
      "url": "https://calbmi.com/",
      "description": "Calculate your Body Mass Index (BMI) instantly. Get personalized health insights, BMI category, ideal weight range, and more.",
      "applicationCategory": "HealthApplication",
      "operatingSystem": "All",
      "browserRequirements": "Requires JavaScript. Requires HTML5.",
      "offers": {
        "@type": "Offer",
        "price": "0.00",
        "priceCurrency": "USD"
      }
    }
    </script>
    <script type="application/ld+json" is:inline>
    {
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "FAQPage",
      "mainEntity": [{
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What is a bmi calculator?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "<p>A <strong>bmi calculator</strong> (Body Mass Index calculator) is a simple health tool that estimates body fat by dividing your weight by your height squared. It classifies your score into standard ranges: Underweight, Normal weight, Overweight, or Obese.</p>"
        }
      }, {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What is my bmi calculator and how do I check it?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "<p>To check \"what is my BMI\", you simply need to input your current weight and height into our free <strong>bmi calculator online</strong>. The tool computes your score instantly and tells you which health category you fall under, along with a chart to show where you stand.</p>"
        }
      }, {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What is my bmi female calculator and how does a women's calculator work?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "<p>A <strong>bmi calculator women</strong> or <strong>bmi calculator female</strong> uses the standard formula <code>weight / height²</code> to compute the index. While the core calculations are identical to men's, interpreting the results for women should account for natural body fat requirements (which are biologically higher in females for hormone regulation) and different ideal weight calculations (Devine formula).</p>"
        }
      }, {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What is my bmi male calculator and does it differ for men?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "<p>A <strong>bmi calculator male</strong> computes your score using your height and weight. For men, ideal body weight is calculated as <code>50 kg + 2.3 kg</code> per inch over 5 feet. Because men generally possess more skeletal muscle mass than women, the score should be interpreted carefully: highly muscular men may receive an \"overweight\" rating even with very low body fat.</p>"
        }
      }, {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How does a bmi calculator work and how to calculate it?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "<p>A BMI calculator works by taking your weight in kilograms and dividing it by your height in meters squared (<code>BMI = kg/m²</code>). To figure it in imperial units, multiply weight in pounds by 703 and divide by height in inches squared: <code>BMI = (lbs × 703) / in²</code>. Our <strong>bmi calculator online</strong> performs these steps automatically for you.</p>"
        }
      }, {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How to use a bmi calculator?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "<p>To use this BMI calculator, simply: 1. Choose your preferred unit system (Metric or Imperial). 2. Enter your age (between 2 and 120 years). 3. Select your gender. 4. Enter your height (in cm or feet/inches) and weight (in kg or lbs). 5. Click Calculate BMI to view your score, category, ideal weight, and next-step calorie suggestions.</p>"
        }
      }, {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Is the bmi calculator accurate and what are its limitations?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "<p>The BMI calculator is a highly accurate tool for screening general health risks across broad populations. However, it is not a direct measurement of body fat percentage. It can be less accurate for athletes (who have dense muscle), pregnant women, children, and elderly individuals who have experienced muscle loss.</p>"
        }
      }, {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How much should I walk according to my bmi calculator results?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "<p>While a BMI calculator doesn't prescribe exact steps, health guidelines recommend at least 150 minutes of moderate-intensity walking per week (about 20-30 minutes daily or 7,000–10,000 steps per day) for maintaining a normal weight. If your calculator shows you are in the overweight or obese category, gradually increasing your walking duration to 300 minutes per week can support safe, sustainable fat loss.</p>"
        }
      }]
    }
    </script>
  </Fragment>

  <!-- Calculator Section -->
  <section id="calculator" class="calc-section" style="padding-top:2.5rem">
    <div class="container">
      <!-- Compact page header -->
      <div class="bmi-page-header scroll-reveal">
        <div class="bmi-page-title-block">
          <span class="hero-badge" style="margin:0">
            <svg width="13" height="13" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><path d="M12 22s8-4 8-10V5l-8-3-8 3v7c0 6 8 10 8 10z"/></svg>
            Free &amp; Accurate
          </span>
          <h1 class="bmi-page-title">Body Mass Index <span class="hero-gradient">Calculator</span></h1>
        </div>
        <p class="bmi-page-sub">Understand your weight status instantly. Based on WHO &amp; CDC standards.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="calc-grid">
        <!-- Input Card -->
        <div class="card calc-card scroll-reveal" style="--reveal-delay:0.05s">
          <div class="card-header">
            <h2 class="card-title">Enter Your Details</h2>
            <p class="card-subtitle">Fill in your measurements below</p>
          </div>

          <!-- Unit Toggle -->
          <div class="unit-toggle-group" role="group" aria-label="Unit system">
            <button class="unit-btn active" id="btnMetric" data-unit="metric" onclick="setUnit('metric')">Metric</button>
            <button class="unit-btn" id="btnImperial" data-unit="imperial" onclick="setUnit('imperial')">Imperial</button>
          </div>

          <form id="bmiForm" class="bmi-form" novalidate>
            <!-- Age -->
            <div class="form-group">
              <label class="form-label" for="ageInput">Age <span class="label-hint">(2 – 120 years)</span></label>
              <div class="input-wrapper">
                <svg class="input-icon" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><circle cx="12" cy="8" r="4"/><path d="M4 20c0-4 3.58-7 8-7s8 3 8 7"/></svg>
                <input class="form-input" type="number" id="ageInput" placeholder="e.g. 25" min="2" max="120" />
                <span class="input-unit">yrs</span>
              </div>
              <div class="form-error" id="ageError"></div>
            </div>

            <!-- Gender -->
            <div class="form-group">
              <label class="form-label">Gender</label>
              <div class="gender-group">
                <label class="gender-option" id="genderMaleLabel">
                  <input type="radio" name="gender" value="male" id="genderMale" checked />
                  <span class="gender-card">
                    <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><circle cx="12" cy="8" r="4"/><path d="M4 20c0-4 3.58-7 8-7s8 3 8 7"/></svg>
                    Male
                  </span>
                </label>
                <label class="gender-option" id="genderFemaleLabel">
                  <input type="radio" name="gender" value="female" id="genderFemale" />
                  <span class="gender-card">
                    <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><circle cx="12" cy="8" r="4"/><path d="M4 20c0-4 3.58-7 8-7s8 3 8 7"/><path d="M9 20h6"/></svg>
                    Female
                  </span>
                </label>
              </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Height (Metric) -->
            <div class="form-group" id="heightMetricGroup">
              <label class="form-label" for="heightCm">Height</label>
              <div class="input-wrapper">
                <svg class="input-icon" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M12 2v20M4 6l3 3M4 12h4M4 18l3-3M20 6l-3 3M20 12h-4M20 18l-3-3"/></svg>
                <input class="form-input" type="number" id="heightCm" placeholder="e.g. 175" min="50" max="280" />
                <span class="input-unit">cm</span>
              </div>
              <div class="form-error" id="heightCmError"></div>
            </div>

            <!-- Height (Imperial) -->
            <div class="form-group hidden" id="heightImperialGroup">
              <label class="form-label">Height</label>
              <div class="imperial-row">
                <div class="input-wrapper">
                  <svg class="input-icon" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M12 2v20"/></svg>
                  <input class="form-input" type="number" id="heightFt" placeholder="5" min="1" max="9" />
                  <span class="input-unit">ft</span>
                </div>
                <div class="input-wrapper">
                  <input class="form-input" type="number" id="heightIn" placeholder="9" min="0" max="11" />
                  <span class="input-unit">in</span>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="form-error" id="heightImperialError"></div>
            </div>

            <!-- Weight (Metric) -->
            <div class="form-group" id="weightMetricGroup">
              <label class="form-label" for="weightKg">Weight</label>
              <div class="input-wrapper">
                <svg class="input-icon" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M12 3a3 3 0 0 1 3 3H9a3 3 0 0 1 3-3z"/><rect x="3" y="6" width="18" height="15" rx="2"/></svg>
                <input class="form-input" type="number" id="weightKg" placeholder="e.g. 70" min="2" max="600" step="0.1" />
                <span class="input-unit">kg</span>
              </div>
              <div class="form-error" id="weightKgError"></div>
            </div>

            <!-- Weight (Imperial) -->
            <div class="form-group hidden" id="weightImperialGroup">
              <label class="form-label" for="weightLbs">Weight</label>
              <div class="input-wrapper">
                <svg class="input-icon" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M12 3a3 3 0 0 1 3 3H9a3 3 0 0 1 3-3z"/><rect x="3" y="6" width="18" height="15" rx="2"/></svg>
                <input class="form-input" type="number" id="weightLbs" placeholder="e.g. 154" min="5" max="1300" step="0.1" />
                <span class="input-unit">lbs</span>
              </div>
              <div class="form-error" id="weightLbsError"></div>
            </div>

            <button type="submit" class="calc-btn" id="calcBtn">
              <svg width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><path d="M9 11l3 3L22 4"/><path d="M21 12v7a2 2 0 0 1-2 2H5a2 2 0 0 1-2-2V5a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h11"/></svg>
              Calculate BMI
            </button>

            <button type="button" class="reset-btn" id="resetBtn" onclick="resetForm()">
              <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M3 12a9 9 0 1 0 9-9 9.75 9.75 0 0 0-6.74 2.74L3 8"/><path d="M3 3v5h5"/></svg>
              Reset
            </button>
          </form>
        </div>

        <!-- Result Card -->
        <div class="card result-card scroll-reveal" style="--reveal-delay:0.15s" id="resultCard">
          <div class="result-placeholder" id="resultPlaceholder">
            <div class="placeholder-icon">
              <svg width="64" height="64" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5">
                <circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/>
                <path d="M12 8v4l3 3"/>
              </svg>
            </div>
            <p class="placeholder-text">Enter your details and click <strong>Calculate BMI</strong> to see your results</p>
          </div>

          <div class="result-content hidden" id="resultContent">
            <!-- Gauge -->
            <div class="gauge-container">
              <svg class="gauge-svg" viewBox="0 0 220 130" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
                <defs>
                  <linearGradient id="gaugeUnderweight" x1="0%" y1="0%" x2="100%" y2="0%">
                    <stop offset="0%" stop-color="#60a5fa"/>
                    <stop offset="100%" stop-color="#3b82f6"/>
                  </linearGradient>
                  <linearGradient id="gaugeNormal" x1="0%" y1="0%" x2="100%" y2="0%">
                    <stop offset="0%" stop-color="#34d399"/>
                    <stop offset="100%" stop-color="#10b981"/>
                  </linearGradient>
                  <linearGradient id="gaugeOverweight" x1="0%" y1="0%" x2="100%" y2="0%">
                    <stop offset="0%" stop-color="#fbbf24"/>
                    <stop offset="100%" stop-color="#f59e0b"/>
                  </linearGradient>
                  <linearGradient id="gaugeObese" x1="0%" y1="0%" x2="100%" y2="0%">
                    <stop offset="0%" stop-color="#f87171"/>
                    <stop offset="100%" stop-color="#ef4444"/>
                  </linearGradient>
                  <filter id="gaugeShadow">
                    <feDropShadow dx="0" dy="2" stdDeviation="3" flood-color="rgba(0,0,0,0.2)"/>
                  </filter>
                </defs>

                <!-- Background arcs -->
                <path d="M 20 115 A 90 90 0 0 1 57.5 36.4" stroke="url(#gaugeUnderweight)" stroke-width="18" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" opacity="0.3"/>
                <path d="M 57.5 36.4 A 90 90 0 0 1 110 25" stroke="url(#gaugeNormal)" stroke-width="18" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" opacity="0.3"/>
                <path d="M 110 25 A 90 90 0 0 1 162.5 36.4" stroke="url(#gaugeOverweight)" stroke-width="18" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" opacity="0.3"/>
                <path d="M 162.5 36.4 A 90 90 0 0 1 200 115" stroke="url(#gaugeObese)" stroke-width="18" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" opacity="0.3"/>

                <!-- Active arcs -->
                <path id="arcUnderweight" d="M 20 115 A 90 90 0 0 1 57.5 36.4" stroke="url(#gaugeUnderweight)" stroke-width="18" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" opacity="0" class="arc-segment"/>
                <path id="arcNormal" d="M 57.5 36.4 A 90 90 0 0 1 110 25" stroke="url(#gaugeNormal)" stroke-width="18" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" opacity="0" class="arc-segment"/>
                <path id="arcOverweight" d="M 110 25 A 90 90 0 0 1 162.5 36.4" stroke="url(#gaugeOverweight)" stroke-width="18" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" opacity="0" class="arc-segment"/>
                <path id="arcObese" d="M 162.5 36.4 A 90 90 0 0 1 200 115" stroke="url(#gaugeObese)" stroke-width="18" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" opacity="0" class="arc-segment"/>

                <!-- Needle -->
                <g id="gaugeNeedle" transform="rotate(0, 110, 115)">
                  <line x1="110" y1="115" x2="110" y2="40" stroke="var(--foreground)" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" filter="url(#gaugeShadow)"/>
                  <circle cx="110" cy="115" r="7" fill="var(--foreground)" filter="url(#gaugeShadow)"/>
                  <circle cx="110" cy="115" r="4" fill="var(--background)"/>
                </g>

                <!-- BMI Value -->
                <text id="gaugeBmiValue" x="110" y="95" text-anchor="middle" class="gauge-value-text" font-size="22" font-weight="800" fill="var(--foreground)">–</text>
                <text x="110" y="108" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="var(--muted-foreground)" font-weight="500">BMI</text>

                <!-- Labels -->
                <text x="10" y="128" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#3b82f6" font-weight="600">Under</text>
                <text x="65" y="28" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#10b981" font-weight="600">Normal</text>
                <text x="157" y="28" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#f59e0b" font-weight="600">Over</text>
                <text x="210" y="128" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#ef4444" font-weight="600">Obese</text>
              </svg>
            </div>

            <!-- Category Badge -->
            <div class="category-badge-container">
              <div class="category-badge" id="categoryBadge">
                <span id="categoryIcon"></span>
                <span id="categoryText">–</span>
              </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Stats Grid -->
            <div class="stats-grid">
              <div class="stat-item">
                <div class="stat-label">Your BMI</div>
                <div class="stat-value" id="statBmi">–</div>
              </div>
              <div class="stat-item">
                <div class="stat-label">Healthy Range</div>
                <div class="stat-value stat-small" id="statRange">18.5–24.9</div>
              </div>
              <div class="stat-item">
                <div class="stat-label">Ideal Weight</div>
                <div class="stat-value stat-small" id="statIdeal">–</div>
              </div>
              <div class="stat-item">
                <div class="stat-label">BMI Prime</div>
                <div class="stat-value" id="statPrime">–</div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Health message -->
            <div class="health-message" id="healthMessage"></div>

            <!-- Weight to Lose/Gain -->
            <div class="weight-diff" id="weightDiff"></div>

            <!-- Calories CTA -->
            <div class="calories-cta" id="caloriesCta">
              <div class="cta-icon">
                <svg width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M12 2a7 7 0 0 1 7 7c0 5-7 13-7 13S5 14 5 9a7 7 0 0 1 7-7z"/><circle cx="12" cy="9" r="2.5"/></svg>
              </div>
              <div class="cta-body">
                <p class="cta-title">What about your daily calories?</p>
                <p class="cta-sub">Find out your TDEE & ideal calorie intake based on your BMI data.</p>
              </div>
              <a href="calories.html" class="cta-btn" id="ctaBtn">
                Calculate
                <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><polyline points="9 18 15 12 9 6"/></svg>
              </a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- BMI Table -->
      <div class="card table-card scroll-reveal" style="--reveal-delay:0.05s" id="tableCard">
        <h3 class="section-title">BMI Classification Table</h3>
        <div class="table-wrapper">
          <table class="bmi-table" id="bmiTable">
            <thead>
              <tr>
                <th>Category</th>
                <th>BMI Range</th>
                <th>Health Risk</th>
                <th>Status</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr data-category="underweight" class="table-row">
                <td><span class="category-dot" style="background:#3b82f6"></span> Underweight</td>
                <td>&lt; 18.5</td>
                <td>Nutritional deficiency</td>
                <td><span class="risk-badge risk-moderate">Moderate</span></td>
              </tr>
              <tr data-category="normal" class="table-row">
                <td><span class="category-dot" style="background:#10b981"></span> Normal weight</td>
                <td>18.5 – 24.9</td>
                <td>Low risk</td>
                <td><span class="risk-badge risk-low">Low</span></td>
              </tr>
              <tr data-category="overweight" class="table-row">
                <td><span class="category-dot" style="background:#f59e0b"></span> Overweight</td>
                <td>25.0 – 29.9</td>
                <td>Increased risk</td>
                <td><span class="risk-badge risk-elevated">Elevated</span></td>
              </tr>
              <tr data-category="obese1" class="table-row">
                <td><span class="category-dot" style="background:#f97316"></span> Obese (Class I)</td>
                <td>30.0 – 34.9</td>
                <td>High risk</td>
                <td><span class="risk-badge risk-high">High</span></td>
              </tr>
              <tr data-category="obese2" class="table-row">
                <td><span class="category-dot" style="background:#ef4444"></span> Obese (Class II)</td>
                <td>35.0 – 39.9</td>
                <td>Very high risk</td>
                <td><span class="risk-badge risk-very-high">Very High</span></td>
              </tr>
              <tr data-category="obese3" class="table-row">
                <td><span class="category-dot" style="background:#9f1239"></span> Obese (Class III)</td>
                <td>&ge; 40.0</td>
                <td>Extremely high risk</td>
                <td><span class="risk-badge risk-extreme">Extreme</span></td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- About Section -->
  <section id="about" class="about-section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <div class="section-badge">What is BMI?</div>
        <h2 class="section-title-lg">Understanding Body Mass Index</h2>
        <p class="section-description">BMI is a widely used screening tool that measures body fat based on height and weight. While it doesn't directly measure body fat, it correlates well with more direct measures of body fat.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="info-grid scroll-reveal" style="--reveal-delay:0.05s">
        <div class="info-card">
          <div class="info-icon" style="--icon-color: #6366f1">
            <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M9 11l3 3L22 4"/><path d="M21 12v7a2 2 0 0 1-2 2H5a2 2 0 0 1-2-2V5a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h11"/></svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="info-title">How BMI Works</h3>
          <p class="info-text">BMI is calculated by dividing your weight in kilograms by the square of your height in meters. The formula: <strong>BMI = kg/m²</strong></p>
        </div>
        <div class="info-card">
          <div class="info-icon" style="--icon-color: #10b981">
            <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M22 11.08V12a10 10 0 1 1-5.93-9.14"/><polyline points="22 4 12 14.01 9 11.01"/></svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="info-title">When to Use BMI</h3>
          <p class="info-text">BMI is a useful screening tool for adults aged 18-65. It helps identify potential weight issues that could lead to health problems.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="info-card">
          <div class="info-icon" style="--icon-color: #f59e0b">
            <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M10.29 3.86L1.82 18a2 2 0 0 0 1.71 3h16.94a2 2 0 0 0 1.71-3L13.71 3.86a2 2 0 0 0-3.42 0z"/><line x1="12" y1="9" x2="12" y2="13"/><line x1="12" y1="17" x2="12.01" y2="17"/></svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="info-title">BMI Limitations</h3>
          <p class="info-text">BMI doesn't account for muscle mass, bone density, or fat distribution. Athletes may have high BMI despite being healthy.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="info-card">
          <div class="info-icon" style="--icon-color: #ec4899">
            <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M20.84 4.61a5.5 5.5 0 0 0-7.78 0L12 5.67l-1.06-1.06a5.5 5.5 0 0 0-7.78 7.78l1.06 1.06L12 21.23l7.78-7.78 1.06-1.06a5.5 5.5 0 0 0 0-7.78z"/></svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="info-title">Beyond BMI</h3>
          <p class="info-text">For a complete picture, consider waist circumference, body fat percentage, and metabolic health markers alongside BMI.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Formula section -->
      <div class="formula-section scroll-reveal" style="--reveal-delay:0.1s">
        <h3 class="formula-title">BMI Formula</h3>
        <div class="formula-cards">
          <div class="formula-card">
            <div class="formula-label">Metric</div>
